{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "962ce6374bc1db0c", "candidate": {"id": "cand-004", "name": "Sarah-Jane Whitmore", "raw_cv": "SARAH-JANE WHITMORE\nsj.whitmore@email.com | London, UK\n\nSENIOR PRODUCT MANAGER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nProduct leader with 8 years of experience in B2B SaaS, focused on PLG and self-serve growth. Track record of scaling products from Series A to Series C. Experienced people manager and cross-functional leader.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nHead of Product \u2014 Workato (Remote, UK) (2022\u2013present)\n- Led a team of 4 PMs across integration and automation product lines\n- Drove 40% ARR growth on the self-serve tier through PLG experiments and activation improvements\n- Partnered with GTM to define ICP and build product-led sales motion\n\nSenior Product Manager \u2014 Spendesk, London (2019\u20132022)\n- Owned the expense management and approval workflow product\n- Shipped automated receipt matching, reducing manual finance team work by 5 hours/week per customer\n- Introduced Mixpanel and built the company's first product analytics framework\n\nProduct Manager \u2014 Trello (Atlassian), London (2017\u20132019)\n- PM for the Power-Ups marketplace; grew active integrations by 120 in 12 months\n\nSKILLS\nProduct-led growth, B2B SaaS, OKRs, roadmapping, user research, SQL, Amplitude, Mixpanel, Figma, people management, enterprise sales partnership\n\nEDUCATION\nMEng Computer Science \u2014 University of Cambridge (2013\u20132017)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen", "raw_linkedin": "Product leader obsessed with building B2B SaaS products that sell themselves. I've spent eight years in workflow automation and spend management software \u2014 from Series A scrappiness to Series C scale. Currently leading product at Workato UK, where I have a team of four PMs and we're building the self-serve motion from scratch. I love PLG, data, and the puzzle of making enterprise software actually delightful. Remote-first but occasionally in London co-working spaces. Open to Head of Product or VP Product roles at growth-stage B2B companies.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Sarah-Jane, thanks for joining us. Tell me about your approach to PLG at Workato.\n\nSarah-Jane: At Workato we had a traditional sales-led model and I was brought in to build a PLG layer alongside it. The first thing I did was run activation experiments \u2014 we had a 14-day trial that most users weren't getting value from in time. We redesigned the first-run experience using data from Amplitude and cut time-to-first-automation from 4 days to 20 minutes. That unlocked a 40% lift in trial-to-paid conversion.\n\nInterviewer: How do you manage your team?\n\nSarah-Jane: I have four direct reports \u2014 three senior PMs and one associate PM I've been mentoring. I focus on clarity of ownership, ambitious but achievable goals, and creating space for them to think strategically rather than just executing tickets. I do monthly strategy sessions with the team and quarterly offsites when we can.\n\nInterviewer: This is a fully remote role. How do you feel about that?\n\nSarah-Jane: I've been remote since 2020 and it suits me very well. I have a proper home office setup and I'm very comfortable running async-first teams. I occasionally work from co-working spaces for the social element, but I don't need to be in an office.\n\nInterviewer: Are you UK based with right to work?\n\nSarah-Jane: Yes, British citizen, no issues there.\n\nInterviewer: And salary?\n\nSarah-Jane: I'm at \u00a392,000 currently. I'd be looking for \u00a395,000 for this role.", "years_experience": 8.0, "skills": ["Product-led growth", "B2B SaaS", "OKRs", "Roadmapping", "User research", "SQL", "Amplitude", "Mixpanel", "Figma", "People management", "Enterprise sales partnership", "Data analysis", "Product analytics"], "industries": ["SaaS", "Workflow automation", "Spend management", "Project management"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.82, "culture_fit_score": 0.8, "constraints": [{"id": "703e0613", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary is \u00a392,000", "canonical_key": "salary_current", "value": 92000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.97, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "374cfa25", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking minimum \u00a395,000 for next role", "canonical_key": "salary_expectation", "value": 95000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "b4973528", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Requires fully remote arrangement; no office requirement", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 0.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": null}, {"id": "b8e17890", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "British citizen with unrestricted right to work in UK", "canonical_key": "right_to_work_uk", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": null}, {"id": "58575968", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Prefers occasional use of co-working spaces for social element", "canonical_key": "occasional_coworking", "value": true, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.8, "currency": null}, {"id": "578f6d5c", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_arrangement", "description": "Strong preference for async-first team culture and management approach", "canonical_key": "async_first_culture", "value": true, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85, "currency": null}, {"id": "ed1d012b", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "role_type", "description": "Open to Head of Product or VP Product roles at growth-stage B2B companies", "canonical_key": "lea